For a pipe of length L with wave‐speed v:

 1. Open–open (A) has displacement antinodes at both ends ⇒  
    fn = n·v/(2L), n = 1,2,3… ⇒ f₁ = v/(2L)

 2. Closed–closed (B) has displacement nodes at both ends ⇒  
    fn = n·v/(2L), n = 1,2,3… ⇒ f₁ = v/(2L)

 3. Open–closed (C) has one antinode and one node ⇒  
    fn = (2n−1)·v/(4L), n = 1,2,3… ⇒ f₁ = v/(4L)

Since v/(4L) is half of v/(2L), pipe C has the lowest possible fundamental, and pipes A and B (which tie with f₁ = v/2L) have the highest.
